	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Recently I had a friend approach me for a 1k or smaller NES game. It is part of a larger project that they are working on, so unfortunately I can't share the ROM or source. I thought I'd post the video here for maybe some discussion on developing tiny games like this, or whatever.<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9QF74FRWnc0">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9QF74FRWnc0</a><!-- m --><br /><br />In total it uses 1,020 bytes. I could've saved more room had I planned ahead and rearranged the chr in a particular way. I might make an attempt at some more of these, because it's fun trying to come up with ways to save a byte here or there : ) Anywho, thar ya are.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
